      "writtenOn": "2021-06-03T18:21:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, this is a pretty hack \u0027n\u0027 slash approach, but I think it should fail pretty gracefully if no lock key is found. Perhaps I should ensure that an unlock_combo is indeed found before arming the autolock, though. I\u0027ll make a quick change after work, it should be pretty easy.\n\nIf you want to try it before I get it added, I\u0027ll comment with it below.\n\nRe: action_code_lookup() - kind of the reason I did this is all the existing code goes in the opposite direction - \"We have the button, find the action\", rather than \"We know the action we want, find the button that will get us there\".",
